d galaxy regime. Thus, we provide evidence that these post merger\ngalaxies passed through a ULIRG/HLIRG phase and are now evolving passively.\nUsing the current and extrapolated past SFR of NGC 34, we infer that the ULIRG\nphase of this galaxy has lasted for at least 150 Myr.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Jul 2008 17:54:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
