minished rates or duty\ncycles (e.g. due to feedback), at z < 20-30. We also present several successful\nassembly models and their LISA detection rates, including a \"maximal\" model\nthat gives the highest rate (~30/yr at z~6) without overproducing the total\nSMBH density.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Jul 2008 16:34:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 28 Apr 2009 12:06:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-02-11"}
